page.title: 01Landscape
page.content: The{landscape}is quite flat as we are near the River Humber bank.There are small groups of trees and many ditches and drains.The area is divided into fields and grassland.Near the river there is visible the flood bank,scrub and water barriers.There are lots of mud banks out passed the low water mark. There are two lighthouses here in our area,one is used still but the other one is disused. Along Thorngumbald Road there is a {gas works}and a{sewage works}which can be seen. On the edge of the village of Paull there is a{football pitch}with a {cricket pitch}near it. There are about six kilometers of river in our D Block unit.
